Iraq Announces to Resume Cooperation With
BAGHDAD , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- Iraq on Saturday allowed unconditional return of U.N. weapons inspectors , an attempt possibly to ward off an imminent U.S. military strike .
Iraq will allow the inspectors of both U.N. Special Commission and the International Atomic Energy Agency to return and resume their daily work , promising all convenience to them .
In a letter to U.N. chief Kofi Annan read on Iraqi TV , Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz said the previous Iraqi decisions made in August and October were only aimed at seeking an end to the suffering of the Iraqi people under the U.N. sanctions .
He said that Saturday 's decision was designed to give a chance to diplomatic solution to the current crisis .
